question:
District category contains Diplomatic Quarter, Arts District, and Legislative District.
Supermarkets category contains Stop & Shop, Aldi (Germany), and PriceRite.
The number of each Diplomatic Quarter 's Aldi (Germany) equals 2 times each Arts District 's Aldi (Germany).
The number of each Arts District 's PriceRite equals 9.
The number of each Arts District 's Aldi (Germany) equals 9.
The number of each Diplomatic Quarter 's PriceRite equals 0.
The number of each Arts District 's Stop & Shop equals 13 times the sum of each Diplomatic Quarter 's Aldi (Germany) and each Arts District 's Aldi (Germany).
The number of each Legislative District 's Stop & Shop equals 10.
The number of each Legislative District 's PriceRite equals 17.
How many Supermarkets does Legislative District have?
solution:
Define each Legislative District 's Stop & Shop as u; So u = 10.
Define each Legislative District 's PriceRite as q; So q = 17.
Define each Legislative District 's Supermarkets as z; So z = u + q = 10 + 17 = 4.
